    From bluez documentation:

    Copy the source file (from remote device) to the
    target file (on local filesystem).

    If an empty target file is given, a name will be
    automatically calculated for the temporary file.

    The returned path represents the newly created transfer,
    which should be used to find out if the content has been
    successfully transferred or if the operation fails.

    The properties of this transfer are also returned along
    with the object path, to avoid a call to GetProperties.
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​org.freedesktop.dbus.types.Variant<?>>[] ListFolder()
    From bluez documentation:

    Returns a dictionary containing information about
    the current folder content.

    The following keys are defined:

    string Name : Object name in UTF-8 format
    string Type : Either "folder" or "file"
    uint64 Size : Object size or number of items in
    folder
    string Permission : Group, owner and other
    permission
    uint64 Modified : Last change
    uint64 Accessed : Last access
    uint64 Created : Creation date

    From bluez documentation:

    Copy the source file (from local filesystem) to the

    The returned path represents the newly created transfer,
    which should be used to find out if the content has been

    The properties of this transfer are also returned along

      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​org.freedesktop.dbus.types.Variant<?>>[] ListFolder() throws BluezFailedException
      From bluez documentation:

      Returns a dictionary containing information about
      the current folder content.

      The following keys are defined:

      string Name : Object name in UTF-8 format
      string Type : Either "folder" or "file"
      uint64 Size : Object size or number of items in
      folder
      string Permission : Group, owner and other
      permission
      uint64 Modified : Last change
      uint64 Accessed : Last access
      uint64 Created : Creation date

    • GetFile

      TwoTuple<org.freedesktop.dbus.DBusPath,​java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​org.freedesktop.dbus.types.Variant<?>>> GetFile​(java.lang.String _targetfile, java.lang.String _sourcefile) throws BluezInvalidArgumentsException, BluezFailedException
      From bluez documentation:

      Copy the source file (from remote device) to the
      target file (on local filesystem).

      If an empty target file is given, a name will be
      automatically calculated for the temporary file.

      The returned path represents the newly created transfer,
      which should be used to find out if the content has been
      successfully transferred or if the operation fails.

      The properties of this transfer are also returned along
      with the object path, to avoid a call to GetProperties.

      Parameters:
      _targetfile -
      _sourcefile -
      Throws:
